《小事情》由[[紅髮艾德|紅髮艾德]]与[[費歐娜·貝文|費歐娜·貝文]]共同创作，其制作则由[[傑克·高斯林|傑克·高斯林]]负责。<ref name=credits>{{cite AV media notes |title=Take Me Home |others=One Direction |date=2012 |type=专辑内页 |publisher=[[賽科音樂|Syco Records]]}}</ref>2012年2月，1世代称有兴趣与-{zh-tw:艾德;zh-hk:希蘭;zh-cn:希兰}-合作创作组合的第2张录音室专辑。<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.capitalfm.com/artists/one-direction/news/ed-sheeran-new-album/ |title=One Direction want to work with Ed Sheeran again on new album |work=Capital FM |publisher=Global Radio |date=2012-02-20 |accessdate=2012-11-12 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120422082146/http://www.capitalfm.com/artists/one-direction/news/ed-sheeran-new-album/ |archivedate=2012-04-22 }}</ref>6月，-{zh-tw:艾德;zh-hk:希蘭;zh-cn:希兰}-公開表示1世代将录制两首他创作的歌曲。<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.mtv.co.uk/news/ed-sheeran/357935-ed-sheeran-working-with-one-direction |title=Ed Sheeran to produce One Direction tracks |work=[[MTV新闻|MTV News]] |publisher=[[維亞康姆|Viacom]] |date=2012-06-25 |accessdate=2012-11-12 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130109103909/http://www.mtv.co.uk/news/ed-sheeran/357935-ed-sheeran-working-with-one-direction |archivedate=2013-01-09 }}</ref>10月15日，[[路易·湯姆林森|路易·湯姆林森]]通過Twitter證實，《青春满屋》的第二支單曲將是《小事情》。<ref name="lout">{{cite web |url=http://www.digitalspy.com/music/news/a430767/one-direction-confirm-new-single-little-things.html |title=One Direction confirm new single 'Little Things' |work=Digital Spy |publisher=Hearst Magazines UK |date=2012-10-15 |accessdate=2012-11-01 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121017021335/http://www.digitalspy.com/music/news/a430767/one-direction-confirm-new-single-little-things.html |archivedate=2012-10-17 }}</ref>同月25日，-{zh-tw:艾德;zh-hk:希蘭;zh-cn:希兰}-在参与英国电台[[Capital_(电台)|Capital FM]]采访时表示：“我十七岁时和一个叫費歐娜·貝文的女孩写了这首歌，但我们把歌弄丢了。我一直与費歐娜保持联系，我们一起做了一些短时的工作并创作出了一些东西，然后大概两个月前，她发给我了一首歌的旋律说：‘噢，你还记得这个吗？’我说：‘肯定啊，我当然记得这个’。我当时正和1世代的男孩们在录音室里，我把它放了出来，他们说：‘我们真喜欢它’。这首歌有我写过的歌中最喜欢的歌词之一。”<ref name="composer">{{cite web |url=http://www.digitalspy.com/music/news/a433343/one-direction-new-single-contains-my-favorite-lyrics-says-ed-sheeran.html |title=One Direction new single contains my favourite lyrics, says Ed Sheeran |work=[[數碼間諜|Digital Spy]] |publisher=Hearst Magazines UK |date=2012-10-25 |accessdate=2012-11-01 |author=Lewis Corner |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121027014540/http://www.digitalspy.com/music/news/a433343/one-direction-new-single-contains-my-favorite-lyrics-says-ed-sheeran.html |archivedate=2012-10-27 }}</ref>

==词曲==
《小事情》是一首中速[[流行音乐|流行]]和[[民俗音樂|民谣]]歌曲，时长3分39秒。<ref name="credits"/><ref name="NYT"/>歌曲以[[G大调|G大调]]创作，<ref name="Sheet">{{cite web |url=http://www.musicnotes.com/sheetmusic/mtdFPE.asp?ppn=MN0111437 |title=One Direction – Little Things|publisher=Musicnotes.com ([[EMI音樂出版|EMI Music Publishing]]) |accessdate=2012-12-08}}</ref>[[拍號|拍號]]為每分鐘110拍。<ref name="Sheet"/>1世代在歌曲中的[[音域|音域]]范围为A<sub>3</sub>到D<sub>5</sub>。<ref name="Sheet"/>歌曲的乐器编成包括[[吉他|吉他和弦]]、[[钢琴|钢琴]]与[[人聲|人聲]]等。<ref name="Sheet" />歌曲利用了[[原音乐|原音]][[固定低音|吉他反覆演奏即興段]]和主唱的转音。<ref name="digital"/><ref name=about/>其歌词围绕着可以讓一個人變得獨特的一些小事情展开。<ref name=about/>2012年9月，在接受[[MTV新闻|MTV新闻]]的采访时，-{zh-tw:艾德;zh-hk:希蘭;zh-cn:希兰}-戏称歌曲“描写的是一个人身上最好的事情，（而这些事情却）是你不想拥有的。”<ref name="MTVNEWS">{{cite web|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/articles/1695868/one-direction-little-things-ed-sheeran.jhtml|title=One Direction's Pal Ed Sheeran Penned Their Next U.K. Single|date=2012-10-19|accessdate=2012-11-01|work=''MTV News''|publisher=Viacom|author=Jocelyn Vena|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121021231932/http://www.mtv.com/news/articles/1695868/one-direction-little-things-ed-sheeran.jhtml|archivedate=2012-10-21}}</ref>他又表示《小事情》是一首有关“欣赏的歌，”最后总结称：“17岁的艾德写了许多首情歌”。<ref name="MTVNEWS"/>

==乐评与奖项==
《小事情》获得了乐评褒贬不一的评价。《[[娱乐周刊|娱乐周刊]]》的格雷迪·史密斯认为歌曲的歌词“方向极度错误”，偏离了1世代的受众喜好。<ref name=ew>{{cite news|author=Grady Smith|title=One Direction release 'Little Things', still 'love' you even though you're fat and terrible|url=http://music-mix.ew.com/2012/10/29/one-direction-little-things/|accessdate=2012-12-08|newspaper=[[娱乐周刊|Entertainment Weekly]]|publisher=[[时代公司|Time Inc.]]|date=2012-10-29|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121205122435/http://music-mix.ew.com/2012/10/29/one-direction-little-things/|archivedate=2012-12-05}}</ref>[[HitFix|HitFix]]的梅琳達·紐曼对歌词内容有着两极化的看法，写道歌词表达了女生希望男生看不见她们身上的缺点或者对她们的缺点视而不见。<ref name=hitfix>{{cite news|author=Melinda Newman|title=One Direction's new song 'Little Things' loves you despite your flaws|url=http://www.hitfix.com/news/listen-one-direction-loves-you-despite-your-flaws-on-new-song-little-things|accessdate=2012-12-08|work=[[HitFix|HitFix]]|publisher=HitFix Inc.|date=2012-10-29|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130107014927/http://www.hitfix.com/news/listen-one-direction-loves-you-despite-your-flaws-on-new-song-little-things|archivedate=2013-01-07}}</ref>《[[獨立報|獨立報]]》的凯特·威尔斯和《[[滾石_(雜誌)|滾石]]》的喬恩·杜兰均批评歌词内容没有针对团体的受众。<ref name="TI">{{cite news |author=Kate Wills |url=http://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/music/reviews/album-one-direction-take-me-home-sony-8303718.html |title=Album: One Direction, Take Me Home (Sony) |work=[[獨立報|The Independent]] |publisher=The Independent Print Limited |date=2012-11-11 |accessdate=2012-11-16 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121116222230/http://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/music/reviews/album-one-direction-take-me-home-sony-8303718.html |archivedate=2012-11-16 }}</ref><ref name="RS">{{cite news |author=Jon Dolan |url=http://www.rollingstone.com/music/albumreviews/take-me-home-20121113 |title=Take Me Home - review |work=[[滾石_(雜誌)|Rolling Stone]] |date=2012-11-14 |accessdate=2012-11-16 |publisher=Jann Wenner |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121116014711/http://www.rollingstone.com/music/albumreviews/take-me-home-20121113 |archivedate=2012-11-16 }}</ref>[[About.com|About.com]]的比尔·兰姆对歌曲的歌词和史密斯持相同看法，但他赞赏了高斯林“优秀的”制作和团体“顶尖的”声音表现。<ref name=about>{{cite news|author=Bill Lamb|title=Review: One Direction - "Little Things"|url=http://top40.about.com/od/singles/gr/One-Direction-Little-Things.htm|accessdate=2012-12-08|publisher=[[纽约时报公司|The New York Times Company]]|work=[[About.com|About.com]]|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121231224400/http://top40.about.com/od/singles/gr/One-Direction-Little-Things.htm|archivedate=2012-12-31}}</ref>{{link-en|BBC音乐|BBC Music}}的艾爾·福斯指出，为追求“歌曲的真实性”，1世代成员在《小事情》中放弃了他们的个性。<ref name="bbcmusic">{{cite news |url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/music/reviews/fh8r |title=Music - Review of One Direction - Take Me Home |work=[[BBC音乐|BBC Music]] |publisher=BBC |date=2012-11-12 |accessdate=2012-11-16 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121115015731/http://www.bbc.co.uk/music/reviews/fh8r |archivedate=2012-11-15 }}</ref>《[[纽约时报|纽约时报]]》的喬恩·卡拉曼尼卡批评-{zh-tw:艾德;zh-hk:希蘭;zh-cn:希兰}-的词曲创作“在受这种优秀的组合控制时却变得反常地粗制滥造”。<ref name="NYT">{{cite news| author=Jon Caramanica| url=https://www.nytimes.com/2012/11/15/arts/music/one-direction-rides-boy-band-wave-with-take-me-home.html?_r=0| work=[[纽约时报|The New York Times]]| publisher=The New York Times Company| title=Riding the Boy Band Wave While It Lasts| date=2012-11-14| accessdate=2012-11-30| deadurl=no| archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121118033945/http://www.nytimes.com/2012/11/15/arts/music/one-direction-rides-boy-band-wave-with-take-me-home.html?_r=0| archivedate=2012-11-18}}</ref>

《[[衛報|衛報]]》的[[亚历克西斯·彼得里迪斯|亚历克西斯·彼得里迪斯]]对《小事情》持不同看法，他认为这首歌曲“明显比专辑的其它歌有着更精致的歌词和情感表达。”<ref name="TG">{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/music/2012/nov/08/one-direction-take-me-review|title=One Direction: Take Me Home – review|publisher=Guardian News and Media|work=[[衛報|The Guardian]]|author=[[亚历克西斯·彼得里迪斯|Alexis Petridis]]|date=2012-11-08|accessdate=2012-11-09|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130926102603/http://www.theguardian.com/music/2012/nov/08/one-direction-take-me-review|archivedate=2013-09-26}}</ref>《[[波士頓環球報|波士頓環球報]]》的编辑莎拉·罗德曼则认为这首“精品”歌曲是专辑中最有价值的一首歌。<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.bostonglobe.com/arts/music/2012/11/27/review-one-direction-take-home/UdKXidfF4usFeraLpdsglL/story.html|title=One Direction, ‘Take Me Home’|work=[[波士頓環球報|The Boston Globe]]|publisher=The New York Times Company|date=2012-11-27|accessdate=2012-11-30|author=Sarah Rodman|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130109014928/http://www.bostonglobe.com/arts/music/2012/11/27/review-one-direction-take-home/UdKXidfF4usFeraLpdsglL/story.html|archivedate=2013-01-09}}</ref>[[Allmusic|Allmusic]]的马特·科拉表示这首抒情歌是“超脱1世代公认青涩的声音中的一首成熟”歌曲。<ref name="allmusic">{{cite news |author=Matt Collar |url=http://www.allmusic.com/album/release/take-me-home-mr0003809780 |title=Take Me Home (CD - Sony Music Distribution #88725475972) |work=[[Allmusic|Allmusic]] |publisher=Rovi Corporation |date=2012-11-11 |accessdate=2012-11-16 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160401130421/http://www.allmusic.com/album/release/take-me-home-mr0003809780 |archivedate=2016-04-01 }}</ref>[[數碼間諜|數碼間諜]]的羅伯特·科普塞则视《小事情》为团体“略微成熟的标志”。<ref name="digital">{{cite web|url=http://www.digitalspy.com.au/music/albumreviews/a436752/one-direction-take-me-home-album-review.html|title=One Direction: 'Take Me Home' - Album review|work=Digital Spy|author=Robert Copsey|date=2012-11-11|accessdate=2012-11-16|publisher=Hearst Magazines UK|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121111073116/http://www.digitalspy.com.au/music/albumreviews/a436752/one-direction-take-me-home-album-review.html|archivedate=2012-11-11}}</ref>

